                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Pātiri Veṇpā</title> appears to be a poem praising the Lord Śiva of <title xml:lang="ta">Tiruppātirippuliyūr</title>, that is <geogName xml:lang="ta">Pāṭaliputtiram</geogName>, in the undivided South Arcot district of Tamil Nadu. The text is incomplete. It stops abruptly at stanza n° 79 at the end of the page (U2, <locus facs="85">f37v</locus>).</p>
                  </summary>
